  "prompt": "Why is it when you bite the inside of our lip, you continue to accidentally bite the same spot?",
  "response": "When you bite the inside of your lip, the bite can cause swelling or a small injury in the area. This swelling can make the spot protrude slightly more than usual, making it more likely that you'll accidentally bite it again. Additionally, the initial injury may create a rough patch or a small sore, which can further increase the likelihood that your teeth will catch on it during chewing or talking.\n\nOnce the area is swollen or irritated, it takes time to heal and return to its normal state. During the healing process, you may need to be extra cautious while eating or speaking to avoid biting the same spot repeatedly. Eating softer foods and being mindful while chewing can help minimize the chances of re-injury and allow the area to heal properly.",
